9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1259, L.D. 1888, “An Act to Combat
10 Organized Criminal Enterprises in Maine”
11 Amend the bill by striking out the title and substituting the following:
12 'Resolve, to Study the Establishment of a New Crime of Racketeering for Drug
13 Offenses and Sex Trafficking'
14 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the title and inserting the following:
15 'Sec. 1. Office of Attorney General to convene working group. Resolved:
16 That the Office of the Attorney General shall convene a working group to study the
17 feasibility of establishing a new crime of racketeering for drug offenses and sex trafficking.
18 Sec. 2. Membership. Resolved: That the working group under section 1 must
19 consist, at a minimum, of the following members:
20 1. The Attorney General or the Attorney General’s designee;
21 2. A representative of a statewide association representing prosecutors;
22 3. A representative of a statewide association representing criminal defense lawyers;
23 4. A representative of a statewide organization advocating for civil liberties;
24 5. A representative of a statewide association representing law enforcement officers;
25 6. A representative of a federal organization that has experience prosecuting federal
26 crimes involving racketeering; and
27 7. A representative of a federal organization that has law enforcement experience that
28 includes investigating federal crimes involving racketeering.
29 Sec. 3. Report. Resolved: That, by January 1, 2026, the Office of the Attorney
30 General shall submit a report that includes the findings and recommendations of the
31 working group under section 1, including suggested legislation, to the Joint Standing
32 Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety. The committee may submit legislation
33 based on the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
