14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, replaces the bill with
1166 a resolve. The amendment directs the Office of the Attorney General to convene a working
1177 group to study the feasibility of establishing the crime of racketeering for drug offenses and
1188 sex trafficking. The office is required to submit a report by January 1, 2026 to the Joint
1199 Standing Committee on Criminal Justice and Public Safety, which may submit legislation
2200 to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature. The amendment removes the
2211 emergency preamble and clause. The amendment also adds an appropriations and
2222 allocations section.
